CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1775823080
OL,3,CBritons warned that bird feeders can
OL,4,Cspread avian diseases
OL,6,FThe house sparrow held on to the top
OL,7,Fspot and the blue tit remained at
OL,8,Fnumber two again this year, followed
OL,9,Fby starling in third, woodpigeon in
OL,10,Ffourth and blackbird in fifth.
OL,12,FWhile starlings jumped from fourth to
OL,13,Fthird place for the most commonly
OL,14,Fspotted species in 2026, it was
OL,15,Flargely because fewer woodpigeons were
OL,16,Freported compared to last year, the
OL,17,FRSPB said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
